-- News Corp.'s Murdoch gets pay raise
-- 
-- Fri Sep 7, 2007 9:19am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/07/us-newscorp-compensation-idUSN0735350320070907

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - News Corp NWSa.N Chairman Rupert Murdoch received a pay raise last fiscal year, boosting his compensation package to $24.3 million, nearly matching the pay of his second in command. 

 Murdoch, who won a deal to buy Wall Street Journal publisher Dow Jones & Co Inc DJ.N, was paid a base salary of $8.1 million in the fiscal year ended June 30, up $3.6 million from the previous year, according to regulatory filings. He also received a bonus of $15.8 million and additional compensation of $356,175. Peter Chernin, News Corp chief operating officer, received a compensation package of $27 million. (Reporting by  Kenneth Li )